<section class="building" id="building">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Our Vision</p>
    <h2 class="section-h" style="color:var(--cream);">Not Just Saved.<br>Built to Last Generations.</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      A Community Land Trust permanently removes land from the speculative market.
      The community owns the ground. Development serves people — not profit.
      Here's what we're building at 7700 SE Stark.
    </p>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🌿</span>
        <h3>Community Land Trust</h3>
        <p>The land held in perpetuity for community benefit. It can never be flipped or redeveloped away from its mission. This is the legal and moral core of the project.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">☀️</span>
        <h3>Year-Round Market Pavilion</h3>
        <p>Industrial shade structures and landscape design make the outdoor market functional in Portland's rain — turning a seasonal venue into a year-round community fixture.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🏗️</span>
        <h3>Mass Timber Community Hub</h3>
        <p>A sustainably built structure housing a commissary kitchen, commercial cold storage, and deep freezers — giving market vendors the infrastructure they need to grow.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🌳</span>
        <h3>Protected Green Space</h3>
        <p>Thoughtful landscape design ensures the lot remains open, welcoming, and ecologically active — green space for Montavilla permanently woven into the neighborhood.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
      <a href="/Montavilla_Community_Land_Trust_Prospectus.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-ghost">
        Read the Full Prospectus →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
